I\'m not part of a Russian botnet
column5: I am not an alt right troll
column6: and I\'m not part of some toxic conspiracy. I\'m a lifelong Star Wars fan and I absolutely loathe this film. It makes a mockery of the story and canon from the first seven films of the canon. Every plot strand from The Force Awakens is either 1.)ignored entirely
column7:
or 2.)given a purposefully anti-climactic ... almost mocking ... resolution.

This film is just an absolute mess of plot holes
column9: and I don\'t like how it seems to purposefully ignore what Star Wars fans probably want to see. It drops traditions like bad habits and scolds us that we shouldn\'t want them in the first place. There is no lightsaber v. lightsaber battle in a numbered Star Wars film. Rey is just an idealized caricature at this point
column10: and I can\'t identify or enjoy her story because she never struggles and is inexplicably wonderful and perfect at everything she does. If I was Mark Hamill I\'d be devastated at what they\'d done to Luke Skywalker. Luke is going to murder a sleeping child
column11: the son of his sister and his best friend
column12: a child sent to him for instruction and entrusted to his care
column13:
because the child is thinking bad thoughts? Are you serious? That\'s really a crucial plot point? Did none of the people working on this story or script ever actually watch a Star Wars movie? The resolution of this film is as stupid and anti-climactic as anything I\'ve ever witnessed.

I have no idea where they go from here. There is nothing left except scorched earth
column15:
and an utter disdain for the Star Wars I-VII.

Oh
column16: and one more thing: I do not need a morality/political lesson in my Star Wars films. Least of all
column18: of all companies. They found time for animal rights and war profiteering political messages in this film
column19: but somehow I don\'t think Disney is going to talk about the evils of exploiting third world labor to make toys for rich westerners
column20: bribing legislators to rob our public domain blind
column21: or outsourcing tech jobs to foreign countries or abusing the H1B visa system. '
